In this article, President Barack Obama issues a proclamation declaring May 10, 2015, as Mother's Day in the United States. He highlights the importance of mothers in society and acknowledges their sacrifices and contributions. The President emphasizes the need for policies that support mothers, including equal pay and access to paid leave and childcare. He urges all Americans to express love and gratitude to their mothers and observe the day with appropriate programs and activities. The article concludes with the official proclamation signed by President Obama.